Even the velvet phase mirrors your “high-bandwidth living semantic layer” idea:
the structure is initially alive, sensitive, nourished, information-rich — then later becomes hardened infrastructure.

There’s also a deeper systems lesson hidden in it:

regenerative systems preserve the generator, not the generated object.

The antler matters less than the regenerative interface that produces it.

That is very Pantheon-coded.